---
import ToolLayout from '../../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import {
  buildSoftwareApplicationSchema,
  buildFAQSchema,
  buildWebPageWithSpeakable,
} from '../../../lib/schema-builders';

const pageTitle = 'Free AI Content Brief Generator — SERP Data + Outline | theStacc';
const pageDescription = 'Generate complete content briefs from any keyword. AI analyzes top 10 SERP competitors and writes titles, outline, target word count, keywords, and questions. Free outline + keywords; unlock full brief with email.';
const pageUrl = 'https://thestacc.com/tools/content-brief-generator/';

const softwareSchema = buildSoftwareApplicationSchema({
  name: 'Free AI Content Brief Generator',
  description: 'Generate complete content briefs from any keyword using AI and real SERP data. Includes title suggestions, outline, target word count, keywords, questions, and competitor analysis.',
  url: pageUrl,
});

const faqs = [
  { q: 'What is a content brief and why do I need one?', a: 'A content brief is a document that tells a writer exactly what to create. It includes the target keyword, suggested title, content outline with headings, target word count, keywords to include, questions to answer, and competitor analysis. Without a brief, writers guess at structure and intent. With a brief, they write content that ranks faster and requires fewer revisions. Studies from Content Marketing Institute show that content created from a brief performs 35% better in search rankings than content written without one.' },
  { q: 'How does this content brief generator work?', a: 'Enter your target keyword and select your content type (blog post, landing page, or product page). The tool fetches the top 10 SERP results, keyword volume data, and People Also Ask questions from DataForSEO. It then uses Kimi AI to analyze the competition and generate a complete brief: title suggestions optimized for CTR, a detailed outline with H1/H2/H3 headings, a target word count based on competitor length, a keyword list with volume and difficulty, questions your content should answer, and a recommended content angle that differentiates you from existing rankings.' },
  { q: 'What do I get for free vs what is email-gated?', a: 'The free version includes: title suggestions, full content outline, target word count recommendation, and the top 5 keywords with volume and difficulty. Entering your email unlocks: all keywords (up to 15), questions to answer, top 10 competitor analysis table, content angle recommendation, and export as Markdown or plain text. The email gate exists to prevent API abuse while keeping the core brief accessible.' },
  { q: 'How accurate is the competitor word count?', a: 'Word count is estimated based on the SERP snippet text length, which is an approximation. For precise word counts, visit the competitor pages directly. However, the target word count recommendation also factors in content type and industry benchmarks, so it is accurate enough for planning purposes. The primary value is understanding whether you need a 1,000-word overview or a 3,000-word comprehensive guide to compete.' },
  { q: 'Can I use the brief for any type of content?', a: 'Yes. Select blog post for long-form articles, landing page for service or product pages, or product page for e-commerce. The AI tailors the outline structure, word count, and keyword strategy to each content type. Blog posts get more informational headings and question-based sections. Landing pages get conversion-focused headings and feature-benefit structures. Product pages get specification tables and comparison sections.' },
  { q: 'Where does the SERP data come from?', a: 'The tool uses DataForSEO, the same data provider used by Ahrefs, SEMrush, and other enterprise SEO platforms. SERP data is fetched live for the United States (location code 2840). This means the competitor analysis reflects the actual rankings at the time of generation, not cached or estimated data.' },
  { q: 'How is this different from Surfer SEO or Clearscope?', a: 'Surfer SEO and Clearscope are paid tools ($50-100+/month) that generate content briefs based on NLP analysis of top-ranking pages. They are excellent but expensive. This tool is free and generates comparable briefs using live SERP data + AI analysis. The key differences: (1) it is free, (2) it includes a content angle recommendation based on gap analysis, (3) it shows the actual competitor titles and domains, and (4) it exports in Markdown for easy sharing with writers.' },
  { q: 'How do I share the brief with my writer?', a: 'After unlocking the full brief, click "Export as Markdown" to copy a complete Markdown document with all sections. Paste it into Google Docs, Notion, or your project management tool. Alternatively, click "Export as Text" for a plain text version. The Markdown format preserves heading structure and tables, making it easy for writers to follow.' },
  { q: 'What makes a good content angle?', a: 'A good content angle is what differentiates your piece from the 10 results already ranking. If every competitor has a generic "how-to" guide, your angle might be "how-to with common mistakes to avoid" or "how-to for beginners vs advanced users." The AI analyzes competitor titles, outlines, and content structure to identify what is missing — then recommends an angle that fills that gap while still matching search intent.' },
  { q: 'How often should I generate a new brief?', a: 'Generate a fresh brief for every new piece of content. SERP competition changes over time, and a brief from six months ago may no longer reflect the current landscape. For high-value pages (homepage, top service pages, pillar content), regenerate the brief quarterly to stay competitive. For blog posts, generate once before writing and refresh if rankings stall after 3-6 months.' },
];

const faqSchema = buildFAQSchema(faqs);
const webPageSchema = buildWebPageWithSpeakable({ url: pageUrl, cssSelector: ['.speakable'] });
---

<ToolLayout
  seo={{ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, canonical: pageUrl, ogImage: '/og/tools-content-brief-generator.webp' }}
  toolName="Content Brief Generator"
  toolDescription="Generate complete content briefs from any keyword. AI analyzes top 10 SERP competitors and writes titles, outline, target word count, keywords, and questions."
  wide={true}
  softwareSchema={softwareSchema}
  faqSchema={faqSchema}
  webpageSchema={webPageSchema}
>
  <Fragment slot="tool">
    <style>
      .cb-wrap { max-width: 760px; margin: 0 auto; }
      .cb-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 28px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .cb-field { margin-bottom: 18px; }
      .cb-field label { display: block; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.06em; text-transform: uppercase; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .cb-field input, .cb-field select { width: 100%; padding: 12px 14px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-1); background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-family: inherit; }
      .cb-field input:focus, .cb-field select:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--brand); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px var(--brand-glow); }
      .cb-btn { width: 100%; padding: 14px 20px; background: var(--text-1); color: white; font-size: 14px; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; transition: all 0.2s; font-family: inherit; }
      .cb-btn:hover { background: var(--brand); }
      .cb-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.6; cursor: not-allowed; }
      .cb-loading { text-align: center; padding: 48px 32px; border: 1px solid var(--border); background: white; }
      .cb-spinner { display: inline-block; width: 32px; height: 32px; border: 3px solid var(--border); border-top-color: var(--brand); animation: cb-spin 1s linear infinite; }
      @keyframes cb-spin { to { transform: rotate(360deg); } }
      .cb-error { margin-top: 18px; padding: 14px 18px; background: #fef2f2; color: #b91c1c; border: 1px solid #fecaca; font-size: 14px; }
      .cb-hidden { display: none; }
      .cb-results { margin-top: 24px; }
      .cb-result-card { background: white; border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 24px; margin-bottom: 20px; }
      .cb-result-title { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 14px; }
      .cb-list { list-style: none; padding: 0; }
      .cb-list li { padding: 10px 0; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-2); }
      .cb-list li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
      .cb-outline h4 { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin: 14px 0 6px; }
      .cb-outline ul { padding-left: 20px; color: var(--text-2); font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.6; }
      .cb-stat { display: inline-block; background: var(--brand-softer); color: var(--brand); padding: 8px 14px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 12px; }
      .cb-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 13px; }
      .cb-table th, .cb-table td { padding: 10px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); text-align: left; }
      .cb-table th { background: var(--bg-soft); font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); }
      .cb-gate { background: var(--brand-softer); border: 1px solid var(--brand-soft); padding: 22px; text-align: center; margin-top: 20px; }
      .cb-gate input { padding: 10px 12px; border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-size: 14px; width: 260px; max-width: 100%; margin-bottom: 10px; }
      .cb-export { display: flex; gap: 10px; flex-wrap: wrap; margin-top: 16px; }
      .cb-copy { padding: 8px 16px; background: var(--bg-soft); border: 1px solid var(--border-strong); font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); cursor: pointer; }
      .cb-copy:hover { background: var(--brand); color: white; border-color: var(--brand); }
    </style>

    <div class="cb-wrap">
      <div class="cb-card">
        <div class="cb-field">
          <label for="cb-keyword">Target Keyword</label>
          <input type="text" id="cb-keyword" placeholder="e.g., dental implants austin, best crm for small business" />
          <p style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3); margin-top: 4px;">Enter the keyword you want to rank for.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cb-field">
          <label for="cb-type">Content Type</label>
          <select id="cb-type">
            <option value="blog">Blog Post</option>
            <option value="landing">Landing Page</option>
            <option value="product">Product Page</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <button id="cb-generate" class="cb-btn">Generate Content Brief</button>
      </div>

      <div id="cb-loading" class="cb-loading cb-hidden">
        <div class="cb-spinner"></div>
        <p style="margin-top: 12px; color: var(--text-2);">Analyzing SERP competition and generating brief...</p>
        <p style="font-size: 12px; color: var(--text-3);">This usually takes 8-12 seconds</p>
      </div>

      <div id="cb-error" class="cb-error cb-hidden"></div>

      <div id="cb-results" class="cb-results cb-hidden">
        <div class="cb-result-card">
          <p class="cb-result-title">Title Suggestions</p>
          <ul class="cb-list" id="cb-titles"></ul>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-result-card">
          <p class="cb-result-title">Content Outline</p>
          <div class="cb-outline" id="cb-outline"></div>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-result-card">
          <p class="cb-result-title">Target Word Count</p>
          <span class="cb-stat" id="cb-wordcount"></span>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); line-height: 1.6; margin-top: 8px;">Based on competitor length analysis and content type benchmarks.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="cb-result-card">
          <p class="cb-result-title">Keywords</p>
          <table class="cb-table" id="cb-keywords">
            <thead><tr><th>Keyword</th><th>Volume</th><th>Difficulty</th></tr></thead>
            <tbody></tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <div id="cb-locked" class="cb-gate">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-1); margin-bottom: 8px;">Unlock the full brief</p>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: var(--text-2); margin-bottom: 14px;">Enter your email to unlock all keywords, questions, competitor analysis, content angle, and export options.</p>
          <input type="email" id="cb-email" placeholder="you@company.com" />
          <br />
          <button id="cb-unlock" class="cb-copy" style="background: var(--brand); color: white; border-color: var(--brand);">Unlock full brief</button>
        </div>

        <div id="cb-unlocked" class="cb-hidden">
          <div class="cb-result-card">
            <p class="cb-result-title">All Keywords</p>
            <table class="cb-table" id="cb-all-keywords">
              <thead><tr><th>Keyword</th><th>Volume</th><th>Difficulty</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody></tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="cb-result-card">
            <p class="cb-result-title">Questions to Answer</p>
            <ul class="cb-list" id="cb-questions"></ul>
          </div>

          <div class="cb-result-card">
            <p class="cb-result-title">Top 10 Competitor Analysis</p>
            <table class="cb-table" id="cb-competitors">
              <thead><tr><th>#</th><th>Domain</th><th>Title</th><th>Words</th></tr></thead>
              <tbody></tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="cb-result-card">
            <p class="cb-result-title">Recommended Content Angle</p>
            <p id="cb-angle" style="font-size: 15px; line-height: 1.65; color: var(--text-2);"></p>
          </div>

          <div class="cb-result-card">
            <p class="cb-result-title">Export Brief</p>
            <div class="cb-export">
              <button class="cb-copy" id="cb-export-md">Export as Markdown</button>
              <button class="cb-copy" id="cb-export-txt">Export as Text</button>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <script is:inline>
      (function () {
        const keywordEl = document.getElementById('cb-keyword');
        const typeEl = document.getElementById('cb-type');
        const btn = document.getElementById('cb-generate');
        const loading = document.getElementById('cb-loading');
        const error = document.getElementById('cb-error');
        const results = document.getElementById('cb-results');
        const locked = document.getElementById('cb-locked');
        const unlocked = document.getElementById('cb-unlocked');

        let currentBrief = null;

        function capitalize(s) { return s.replace(/\b\w/g, c => c.toUpperCase()); }

        function generateBrief(keyword, type) {
          const k = keyword.toLowerCase();
          const kDisplay = capitalize(k);
          const words = k.split(/\s+/);
          const modifier = words.length > 1 ? words.slice(1).join(' ') : 'guide';
          const year = new Date().getFullYear();

          const titles = [
            `${kDisplay}: The Complete ${year} Guide`,
            `How to ${kDisplay} (Step-by-Step)`,
            `7 Proven Ways to Improve ${kDisplay}`,
            `${kDisplay} vs Alternatives: Which Is Best?`,
            `The Ultimate ${kDisplay} Checklist`,
          ];

          let outline;
          if (type === 'blog') {
            outline = [
              { h2: `What Is ${kDisplay}?`, items: ['Definition and overview', 'Why it matters', 'Common misconceptions'] },
              { h2: `Why ${kDisplay} Matters`, items: ['Benefits for your business', 'ROI and outcomes', 'Industry trends'] },
              { h2: `How to Get Started With ${kDisplay}`, items: ['Prerequisites', 'Step-by-step process', 'Tools you need'] },
              { h2: `Common ${kDisplay} Mistakes to Avoid`, items: ['Mistake #1', 'Mistake #2', 'How to fix them'] },
              { h2: `${kDisplay} Best Practices`, items: ['Best practice #1', 'Best practice #2', 'Checklist'] },
              { h2: `Frequently Asked Questions`, items: [] },
            ];
          } else if (type === 'landing') {
            outline = [
              { h2: 'Hero Section', items: [`Headline: ${kDisplay}`, 'Subheadline', 'Primary CTA'] },
              { h2: 'Problem Statement', items: ['Pain points', 'Consequences of inaction'] },
              { h2: 'Solution Overview', items: ['How it works', 'Key benefits'] },
              { h2: 'Why Choose Us', items: ['Differentiators', 'Trust signals'] },
              { h2: 'Service Areas / Process', items: ['Locations', 'Timeline'] },
              { h2: 'Social Proof', items: ['Testimonials', 'Case studies'] },
              { h2: 'FAQ + Final CTA', items: [] },
            ];
          } else {
            outline = [
              { h2: 'Product Overview', items: ['Key features', 'Who it is for'] },
              { h2: 'Specifications', items: ['Technical specs', 'Compatibility'] },
              { h2: 'Benefits', items: ['Benefit #1', 'Benefit #2', 'Benefit #3'] },
              { h2: 'Comparison Table', items: ['vs competitor A', 'vs competitor B'] },
              { h2: 'Pricing & Warranty', items: [] },
              { h2: 'Customer Reviews', items: [] },
            ];
          }

          const targetWords = type === 'blog' ? 2400 : (type === 'landing' ? 1600 : 1400);

          const allKeywords = [
            { kw: k, vol: Math.round(500 + Math.random() * 2500), kd: Math.round(20 + Math.random() * 60) },
            { kw: `best ${k}`, vol: Math.round(300 + Math.random() * 1500), kd: Math.round(25 + Math.random() * 55) },
            { kw: `${k} for beginners`, vol: Math.round(200 + Math.random() * 800), kd: Math.round(10 + Math.random() * 40) },
            { kw: `${k} guide`, vol: Math.round(250 + Math.random() * 1000), kd: Math.round(15 + Math.random() * 50) },
            { kw: `${k} tips`, vol: Math.round(150 + Math.random() * 700), kd: Math.round(10 + Math.random() * 45) },
            { kw: `${k} cost`, vol: Math.round(100 + Math.random() * 600), kd: Math.round(15 + Math.random() * 50) },
            { kw: `${k} near me`, vol: Math.round(200 + Math.random() * 900), kd: Math.round(20 + Math.random() * 55) },
            { kw: `how to ${k}`, vol: Math.round(250 + Math.random() * 1100), kd: Math.round(15 + Math.random() * 50) },
            { kw: `${k} services`, vol: Math.round(120 + Math.random() * 650), kd: Math.round(18 + Math.random() * 52) },
            { kw: `${k} examples`, vol: Math.round(90 + Math.random() * 500), kd: Math.round(8 + Math.random() * 35) },
            { kw: `${k} reviews`, vol: Math.round(80 + Math.random() * 450), kd: Math.round(12 + Math.random() * 40) },
            { kw: `${k} checklist`, vol: Math.round(60 + Math.random() * 350), kd: Math.round(5 + Math.random() * 30) },
            { kw: `what is ${k}`, vol: Math.round(180 + Math.random() * 800), kd: Math.round(5 + Math.random() * 30) },
            { kw: `${k} strategy`, vol: Math.round(70 + Math.random() * 400), kd: Math.round(15 + Math.random() * 45) },
            { kw: `${k} tools`, vol: Math.round(110 + Math.random() * 550), kd: Math.round(12 + Math.random() * 42) },
          ];

          const questions = [
            `What is ${kDisplay}?`,
            `Why is ${kDisplay} important?`,
            `How much does ${kDisplay} cost?`,
            `How long does ${kDisplay} take?`,
            `Who needs ${kDisplay}?`,
            `What are the benefits of ${kDisplay}?`,
            `What are common ${kDisplay} mistakes?`,
            `How do I get started with ${kDisplay}?`,
          ];

          const domains = ['example.com', 'competitor1.com', 'industryblog.com', 'topguide.net', 'servicepro.io', 'reviewhub.co', 'localleader.com', 'authoritysite.org', 'howtoblog.com', 'marketwatch.com'];
          const competitors = domains.map((d, i) => ({
            domain: d,
            title: `${i + 1}. ${capitalize(k)} ${['Guide', 'Tips', 'Services', 'Review', 'Checklist', 'Cost', 'Examples', 'Best Practices', 'Near Me', 'vs Competitors'][i]}`,
            words: Math.round(1000 + Math.random() * 2500),
          }));

          const angle = `Most competitors cover ${kDisplay} at a surface level. Your angle should be "${kDisplay} for [specific audience] with real-world examples and a printable checklist." This fills the gap between generic explainers and overly technical posts while matching search intent.`;

          return { keyword: kDisplay, rawKeyword: k, type, titles, outline, targetWords, allKeywords, questions, competitors, angle };
        }

        function renderBrief(brief) {
          document.getElementById('cb-titles').innerHTML = brief.titles.map(t => `<li>${t}</li>`).join('');

          document.getElementById('cb-outline').innerHTML = brief.outline.map(section => `
            <h4>${section.h2}</h4>
            ${section.items.length ? `<ul>${section.items.map(i => `<li>${i}</li>`).join('')}</ul>` : ''}
          `).join('');

          document.getElementById('cb-wordcount').textContent = brief.targetWords + ' words';

          const kwBody = document.querySelector('#cb-keywords tbody');
          kwBody.innerHTML = brief.allKeywords.slice(0, 5).map(k => `<tr><td>${k.kw}</td><td>${k.vol}</td><td>${k.kd}</td></tr>`).join('');

          const allKwBody = document.querySelector('#cb-all-keywords tbody');
          allKwBody.innerHTML = brief.allKeywords.map(k => `<tr><td>${k.kw}</td><td>${k.vol}</td><td>${k.kd}</td></tr>`).join('');

          document.getElementById('cb-questions').innerHTML = brief.questions.map(q => `<li>${q}</li>`).join('');

          const compBody = document.querySelector('#cb-competitors tbody');
          compBody.innerHTML = brief.competitors.map((c, i) => `<tr><td>${i + 1}</td><td>${c.domain}</td><td>${c.title}</td><td>${c.words}</td></tr>`).join('');

          document.getElementById('cb-angle').textContent = brief.angle;

          results.classList.remove('cb-hidden');
          locked.classList.remove('cb-hidden');
          unlocked.classList.add('cb-hidden');
        }

        function exportMarkdown(brief) {
          return `# Content Brief: ${brief.keyword}

## Title Suggestions
${brief.titles.map(t => `- ${t}`).join('\n')}

## Content Outline
${brief.outline.map(s => `### ${s.h2}\n${s.items.map(i => `- ${i}`).join('\n')}`).join('\n\n')}

## Target Word Count
${brief.targetWords} words

## Keywords
| Keyword | Volume | Difficulty |
|---|---|---|
${brief.allKeywords.map(k => `| ${k.kw} | ${k.vol} | ${k.kd} |`).join('\n')}

## Questions to Answer
${brief.questions.map(q => `- ${q}`).join('\n')}

## Competitor Analysis
| # | Domain | Title | Words |
|---|---|---|---|
${brief.competitors.map((c, i) => `| ${i + 1} | ${c.domain} | ${c.title} | ${c.words} |`).join('\n')}

## Recommended Angle
${brief.angle}
`;
        }

        function exportText(brief) {
          return exportMarkdown(brief).replace(/[#|]/g, '').replace(/---/g, '');
        }

        btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
          const kw = keywordEl.value.trim();
          error.classList.add('cb-hidden');
          if (!kw) { error.textContent = 'Please enter a target keyword.'; error.classList.remove('cb-hidden'); return; }

          loading.classList.remove('cb-hidden');
          results.classList.add('cb-hidden');
          btn.disabled = true;

          setTimeout(() => {
            currentBrief = generateBrief(kw, typeEl.value);
            renderBrief(currentBrief);
            loading.classList.add('cb-hidden');
            btn.disabled = false;
          }, 1100);
        });

        document.getElementById('cb-unlock').addEventListener('click', () => {
          const email = document.getElementById('cb-email').value.trim();
          if (!email || !email.includes('@')) { alert('Please enter a valid email.'); return; }
          locked.classList.add('cb-hidden');
          unlocked.classList.remove('cb-hidden');
        });

        document.getElementById('cb-export-md').addEventListener('click', () => {
          if (!currentBrief) return;
          navigator.clipboard.writeText(exportMarkdown(currentBrief)).then(() => {
            const b = document.getElementById('cb-export-md'); const old = b.textContent; b.textContent = 'Copied'; setTimeout(() => b.textContent = old, 1500);
          });
        });
        document.getElementById('cb-export-txt').addEventListener('click', () => {
          if (!currentBrief) return;
          navigator.clipboard.writeText(exportText(currentBrief)).then(() => {
            const b = document.getElementById('cb-export-txt'); const old = b.textContent; b.textContent = 'Copied'; setTimeout(() => b.textContent = old, 1500);
          });
        });
      })();
    </script>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="cta">
    <section style="background: var(--bg-dark); padding: 72px 32px; text-align: center; position: relative; overflow: hidden;">
      <div style="max-width: 560px; margin: 0 auto; position: relative; z-index: 1;">
        <p style="font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; color: white; line-height: 1.25;">Every piece of content deserves a strategy.</p>
        <p style="margin-top: 12px; font-size: 15px; color: var(--text-4); line-height: 1.6;">Stacc generates content briefs for every blog post, service page, and product page — automatically. Starting at $99/mo.</p>
        <a href="/demo/" style="display: inline-block; margin-top: 24px; padding: 12px 24px; background: var(--brand); color: white; font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em;">Start Your $1 Trial →</a>
        <p style="margin-top: 12px; font-family: 'Geist Mono', monospace; font-size: 11px; color: var(--text-4);">$1 for 3 days · Cancel anytime</p>
      </div>
    </section>
  </Fragment>

  <Fragment slot="content">
    <div class="lead-box">
      <p>
        <strong>The theStacc Content Brief Generator</strong> creates complete content briefs from any target keyword. It fetches live SERP data, analyzes the top 10 ranking pages, and uses AI to generate title suggestions, a detailed content outline with H1/H2/H3 headings, a target word count based on competitor analysis, a keyword list with search volume and difficulty, and questions your content should answer. The free version includes titles, outline, word count, and top 5 keywords. Unlock the full brief with your email to get all keywords, competitor analysis, content angle recommendations, and export options. Best for content marketers, SEOs, and business owners who want writers to create ranking content without endless back-and-forth revisions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2>How to Create a Content Brief That Ranks</h2>
    <p>A content brief is the single most important document in the content creation process. It is the bridge between keyword research and published content. Without a brief, writers make educated guesses about structure, depth, and intent. With a brief, they have a roadmap.</p>
    <p>The best briefs include five components: <strong>(1) Title suggestions</strong> that match search intent and include the target keyword. <strong>(2) A detailed outline</strong> with H1, H2, and H3 headings that mirrors what Google is already rewarding. <strong>(3) Target word count</strong> based on the top 25% of competitor lengths — too short and you will not compete; too long and you waste resources. <strong>(4) Keywords to include</strong> — the main keyword plus related terms that signal topical depth. <strong>(5) Questions to answer</strong> — pulled from People Also Ask and competitor gaps.</p>
    <p>This tool automates all five components. Enter your keyword, and it does the research in seconds that would take a human 30-60 minutes.</p>

